EFFECTIVE DATE……………………………………………………………………………………………………. 10 RATE SUMMARY…………………………………………………………………………………………………… 11 UNITED STATES OF AMERICA BEFORE THE FEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSION STATEMENT OF OPERATING CONDITIONS FOR INTERRUPTIBLE TRANSPORTATION SERVICE RENDERED UNDER SECTION 311 (a) (2) OF THE NATURAL GAS POLICY ACT OF 1978 AND THE RULES AND REGULATIONS ADOPTED THEREUNDER Southcross Gulf Coast Transmission Ltd. (“SGCT”), a Texas Limited Partnership, is filing this statement in accordance with Section 284.123 (e) of the regulations of the regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (“Commission”) which directs SGCT to state upon what general conditions SGCT will provide transportation services to qualified Shippers pursuant to Section 311 (a) (2) of the Natural Gas Policy Act of 1978 (“NGPA”), as implemented by Subpart C of Part 284 of the Commission’s regulations.1/ This Statement is not meant to amend, modify, or supersede provisions contained in Transportation Service Agreements entered into by SGCT. I. General Provisions: Nondiscriminatory Service SGCT will provide transportation service to qualified Shippers, without undue discrimination or preference within the meaning of 18 C.F.R. § 284.9, including undue discrimination or preference in the quality of service provided, the duration of service, the categories, prices, or volumes of natural gas to be transported, customer classification, or undue discrimination or preference of any kind, subject to the conditions set forth in this Statement, or such reasonable conditions as may be established from time to time by SGCT without undue discrimination or preference, and subject to applicable legal and regulatory requirements and terms contained in Transportation Service Agreements between SGCT and Shippers. II. Quality A. Standards: SGCT may decline to provide transportation service to a Shipper it he gas to be transported is not commercially free of dust, hydrocarbon liquids, water and any _______________________ 1/ In filing this Statement, SGCT is not, and shall not be deemed to be, submitting to, or conceding jurisdiction of the Commission over SGCT regarding matters relating to this Statement, and SGCT reserves the right to challenge or contest the Commission’s jurisdiction over SGCT in any action, suit, regulatory proceeding or court proceeding. 2 other substances separated from the gas, or if such gas does not conform, at a minimum, to the following specifications: (1) Contain not more than five (5) grains of total sulphur not more than one-fourth (1/4) grain or hydrogen sulfide and one (1) grain or mercaptan sulphur per one hundred (100) standard cubic feet; (2) Contain no oxygen; (3) Contain not more than three percent (3%) by volume of a combined total of carbon dioxide and nitrogen components; provided, however, that the total carbon dioxide content shall not exceed two percent (2%) by volume; (4) Have a temperature of not less than forty degrees (40º) Fahrenheit not more than one hundred twenty degrees (120º) Fahrenheit; (5) Contain not more than seven (7) pounds of entrained water vapor per one million (1,000,000) cubic feet of gas; and (6) Have a gross heating value of not less than nine hundred fifty (950) nor more than one thousand one hundred fifty (1150) Btu per cubic foot, saturated with water vapor at a temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60º F) and at a pressure equivalent to fourteen and sixty-five hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.65 psia). B. Measurement: The measurement and tests for quality of gas tendered to SGCT, which shall be performed at SGCT’s reasonable discretion and at Shipper’s expense, shall be governed by the following: (1) The volume shall be measured by orifice meters or other measuring device; operated by SGCT or its agent, and computations made as prescribed in Gas Measurement Committee Report No. 3 (Revised 1975) of the American Gas Association, as such report may be amended or revised from time to time; (2) The unit of volume for purposes of measurement shall be one (1) cubic foot of gas at a temperature base of sixty degrees (60º) Fahrenheit and a pressure base of fourteen and sixty-five one hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.65 psia); (3) Temperature shall be determined by a recording thermometer continuously used and installed so as to record property the temperature of the gas being measured; (4) The specific gravity of the gas shall be determined by the use of a recording gravitometer or a portable specific gravity balance, of standard manufacture and properly installed, or by any other standard device or method mutually acceptable to the parties; 3 (5) The supercompressibility of the gas (deviation from the laws for ideal gases) shall be determined by SGCT using a continuous or spot sampler by one of the following methods: a. By use of the table of formulae published in conjunction with the 1978 First Edition of the American National Standard Institute’s Report on “Orifice Metering of Natural Gas” (ANSI/API 2530”). Determinations of the mol degree of N2 and CO2 in the gas will be made within thirty (30) days of commencement on deliveries and at least quarterly thereafter. The mol degree of N2 and CO2 thus determined will be used to determine the supercompressibility factors during the ensuing period, with correction for specific gravity, temperature and pressure; or b. If agreeable to the parties, by use of a Burnett-type apparatus. Such determination shall be made within thirty (30) days of commencement of deliveries and at least quarterly thereafter. (6) The gross heating value of the gas shall be determined by tests made by taking samples of the gas at the Point(s) of Delivery and Redelivery at such times as may be designated by SGCT or its agent. Said samples shall have the British Thermal Unit content per cubic foot determined by an accepted type of recording calorimeter or chromatograph or other acceptable method at a temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60º F) when saturated with water vapor and at a pressure equivalent to fourteen and sixty-five one hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.65 psia). The gross heating value so determined shall be corrected from the conditions of testing to that of the actual condition of the gas as delivered, expressed in Btu’s per cubic foot, and reported at a pressure base of fourteen and sixty-five hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.65 psia); provided, however, if the gas as delivered contains seven (7) pounds of water vapor or less per million (1,000,000) cubic feet, such gas shall be deemed to be dry; (7) Tests to determine sulphur, hydrogen sulfide, oxygen, carbon dioxide, nitrogen, and water content shall be made by approved standard methods in general use by the gas industry. Such tests shall be made as deemed necessary by SGCT. III. Pressure A. Deliveries of gas to SGCT by Shipper at the Point(s) of Delivery under the Transportation Service Agreement shall be a pressure sufficient to overcome the operating pressure existing in SGCT’s facilities at such point(s) from time to time, but not in excess of the maximum allowable operating pressure of SGCT’s facilities at such point(s). SGCT shall not be required to provide compression service to effectuate such deliveries by Shipper. 4 B. SGCT shall deliver gas at the Point(s) of Redelivery to or for the account of Shipper at the pressure which shall be available from time to time in SGCT’s pipeline system after required measurement, flow control and/or regulation. SGCT shall not be required to provide compression service to effectuate redelivery. IV. Request for Transportation Service; Transportation Service Agreement A. SGCT may decline to provide transportation service if Shipper has not made an appropriate request to SGCT for transportation service and has not executed a Transportation Service Agreement with SGCT. In requesting transportation service, Shipper shall provide to SGCT, in writing, the following: (1) Shipper – the name, address, telephone number and principal place of business of the proposed Shipper; (2) Gas Quantities – statement of the total and maximum daily quantities of gas, or estimate thereof, to be transported by SGCT for Shipper for each Point of Delivery and Redelivery; provided however, that daily quantities of gas at each Point of Delivery and Redelivery meet the maximum volume requirement as specified in Paragraph D of Article V. hereof; (3) Point(s) of Delivery a. identification of each Point of Delivery of the gas to SGCT’s facilities; and b. the name and classification (i.e. interstate pipeline, local distribution company, etc.) of each entity owning and/or transporting the gas prior to delivery to SGCT’s facilities; (4) Original Source of Gas – the location (i.e. state) of the original source of the gas; (5) Point(s) of Redelivery a. identification of each Point of Redelivery of the gas by SGCT; b. the name and classification (i.e. interstate pipeline, local distribution company, etc.) of each entity owning and/or transporting the gas subsequent to redelivery by SGCT; (6) Ultimate Delivery Point of Gas – the location (i.e. state) of the ultimate delivery point of the gas; (7) Term of Service a. the date service is requested to commence; b. the date service is requested to terminate; 5 (8) Assurance of Third Party Transportation – Shipper shall provide SGCT a copy of a Transportation Service Agreement for transportation of the gas (or equivalent, such as a letter of intent) executed by each third party transporter necessary to effectuate delivery of the gas from its origin to the entity ultimately receiving the gas; and proof that all third party transporters have obtained, or reasonably in advance of the commencement of service will obtain, all Federal and State approvals necessary to effectuate the transportation service; or shall provide such other documentation as required to reasonably satisfy SGCT that necessary third party transportation has been or will be obtained; (9) Warranty of Title to Gas – Shipper for itself, its successors, and assigns shall warrant to SGCT that it will at the time of delivery to SGCT for transportation have good and merchantable title to all gas so delivered free and clear of all liens, encumbrances and claims. Shipper will indemnify SGCT and save it harmless from all suits, actions, regulatory proceedings, debts, damages, costs, losses and expenses (including reasonable attorney fees) arising from or out of adverse claims relating to said gas (including, without limitation, claims for any royalties, taxes, license fees or charges applicable to such gas or to the delivery thereof to SGCT for transportation) of any or all persons. If, subsequent to commencement of the transportation service, SGCT has reason to question Shipper’s warranty of title to said gas, SGCT may refuse to accept Shipper’s tendered deliveries and may continue such refusal until Shipper satisfies SGCT of its warranty of title; (10) Warranty of Eligibility for Transportation – Shipper for itself, its successors, and assigns shall warrant to SGCT that all gas delivered to SGCT for transportation is eligible for transportation in interstate commerce under applicable regulations or orders of the FERC or any other legal or regulatory body with jurisdiction. Shipper shall indemnify SGCT and save it harmless from all suits, actions, regulatory proceedings, damages, costs, losses, or expenses (including reasonable attorneys fees) arising from breach of this warranty; (11) Warranty of Compliance with NGPA §311 – Shipper for itself, its successors, and assigns shall warrant to SGCT that the requested transportation service is on behalf of an interstate pipeline or a local distribution company served by an interstate pipeline as defined in the NGPA, and that the requested transportation service is permitted by, and satisfies all requirements of, Section 311 (a) (2) of the NGPA and all rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; and Shipper shall indemnify SGCT and save it harmless from all sits, actions, regulatory proceedings, damages, costs, losses or expenses (including reasonable attorneys fees) arising from breach of this warranty; B. Unless waived by SGCT without undue discrimination or preference, a request for transportation service shall be considered a nullity and shall be ineffective to hold a priority for transportation service if a Transportation Service Agreement with SGCT for the requested transportation service is not executed within twenty (20) days of the date the request is received by SGCT. 6 V. Operating Conditions: Priority of Service A. Transportation services performed by SGCT under Section 311 of the NGPA shall be made available to Shippers based upon the receipt, in chronological order, or a valid request for transportation pursuant to the provisions of this Statement, subject to the conditions contained in this Statement, the terms contained in applicable Transportation Service Agreements, the availability of sufficient system capacity and other operational constraints. B. All transportation services provided by SGCT shall be fully interruptible. C. In carrying out its day-to-day operations, SGCT in its reasonable discretion shall determine the manner in which its facilities will be utilized and in which services or requested services will be provided. D. SGCT shall not be required to provide transportation service for any Shipper unless the daily minimum quantity is 2,000 MMBTU or greater at each Point of Delivery and Redelivery. E. SGCT shall not be required to provide transportation service if: (1) providing such service would cause SGCT to have insufficient capacity or operational capability to meet all existing or future intrastate contractual obligations; or (2) providing such service would affect or increase operational requirements of SGCT with its suppliers, including but not limited to obligations regarding drainage, or (3) providing such service would require SGCT to purchase or increase purchases of gas; or (4) providing such service would, in SGCT’s reasonable judgment, be detrimental to SGCT’s system operations, or (5) all facilities (including those of intermediate transporters) necessary to effectuate the transportation are not in existence at the time the request for transportation is made; or (6) Shipper fails to comply with the terms of this Statement, the terms of its Transportation Service Agreement, or applicable legal and regulatory provisions. F. Availability of SGCT’s facilities to Shipper is subject to all restrictions and constraints imposed upon SGCT’s ownership or joint ownership of facilities. SGCT shall be under no obligation to construct pipeline, compression or any other facilities for the receipt, transportation or redelivery of gas hereunder. G. SGCT shall not be required to change its system operating pressure, or to alter the direction of gas flow, the gas load, or other operations or utilization of its facilities in order to receive, transport or redeliver gas hereunder. 7 H. In order that SGCT may maintain its status as a non-jurisdictional intrastate pipeline, and may be fully cognizant of any acts or events that could affect its status or operations, Shipper shall obtain advance approval from SGCT before SGCT’s facilities are used to transport for any party other than specified in Shipper’s original request for transportation service. I. Notwithstanding anything in this Statement to the contrary, SGCT shall not be obligated to continue the transportation services described herein if SGCT determines, in its sole discretion and judgment, that such services would at any time prevent SGCT from operating its system at its maximum potential throughput, or would not be economically beneficial to SGCT. VI. Financial Viability of Shipper SGCT may decline to provide a requested transportation service or to continue to provide an existing transportation service, for any Shipper which: (1) has applied for bankruptcy; (2) is insolvent; (3) is in arrears with SGCT, or its affiliated companies, for charges for any service provided by SGCT or such affiliate(s); or (4) otherwise fails to demonstrate sufficient creditworthiness, as determined in SGCT’s sole judgment. SGCT shall have the continuing right to review Shipper’s creditworthiness, from time to time, during the term of the Transportation Service Agreement with Shipper. If at any time SGCT determines, in its sole judgment, that Shipper is not creditworthy, SGCT shall have the right to (i) require Shipper to prepay for the requested transportation service and/or pay in full for any existing service, including any arrearage, and/or (ii) require Shipper to furnish to SGCT sufficient surety bond or other sufficient security which, in the sole judgment of SGCT, provides assurance that SGCT will be fully and timely compensated for service, and/or (iii) suspend such existing transportation service upon at least two (2) days’ prior written notice to Shipper. VII. Rates The rate to be paid by Shipper for service provided hereunder shall be agreed to by Shipper and SGCT, provided, however, that such rate shall not exceed the maximum rate approved for the service. VIII. Regulatory Fees Shippers shall pay in advance to SGCT all fees required by the Commission or any other regulatory body related to service provided pursuant to this Statement, including but not limited 8 to filing, reporting, application fees, and including such fees that SGCT may be required to reimburse to third parties. IX. Balancing Balancing of receipt and redelivery of gas by SGCT shall be governed by the following: A. Balancing of Deliveries 1. At least forty-eight (48) hours prior to the initial tender of gas to SGCT for Shipper’s account, Shipper’s dispatcher or designee shall notify SGCT’s dispatcher(s) of the quantity of gas Shipper desires to have transported and the date upon which initiation of such transportation is desired. On the date specified in Shipper’s notice, and until changed by subsequent forty-eight (48) hours’ prior notice to SGCT, SGCT shall receive on an interruptible basis from, shall transport for, and shall redeliver to or for the account of Shipper the quantity of gas so nominated. SGCT agrees to waive any part of the forty-eight (48) hours notice if, in its sole judgment, operating conditions permit such waiver. The daily quantities of gas so requested shall be taken/delivered by SGCT by or for the account of Shipper at the Point(s) of Delivery and Redelivery at a substantially constant hourly and daily rate. Any notices given pursuant to this paragraph may be given in writing or verbally if confirmed in writing within five (5) days. 2. Shipper’s dispatcher or designee shall immediately notify SGCT’s dispatcher(s) of any changes in operational conditions on Shipper’s, or its representatives’ system(s) that will cause hourly rate variations in deliveries or redeliveries for Shipper’s account. The extent of such permissible hourly rate variations shall be at the sole discretion of SGCT’s dispatcher(s). B. Balancing Charge: 1. A charge of $1.00/MMBtu per day shall be assessed to any Shipper which SGCT determines has, through its failure to exercise reasonable diligence, a. taken or caused to be taken from SGCT quantities of gas in excess of 103% of the quantities delivered, after appropriate reductions, to SGCT; or b. delivered or caused to be delivered to SGCT, after appropriate reductions, quantities in excess of 103% of the quantities taken from SGCT; or c. delivered or caused to be delivered to SGCT quantities of gas in excess of 103% of Shipper’s maximum daily quantities; or d. taken or caused to be taken from SGCT quantities of gas in excess of 103% of Shipper’s maximum daily quantities; or e. failed to deliver, or failed to cause to be delivered, to SGCT at least 97% of the quantities scheduled to be delivered to SGCT in 9 accordance with the scheduling provisions of Shipper’s Transportation Service Agreement. In addition to such charge, SGCT shall have the right, upon notice, to terminate service to any Shipper against whom said charge is assessed for a total of five (5) days or more in any calendar year. X. Termination of Service Notwithstanding any other provision of this Statement, SGCT’s obligation to provide transportation service pursuant to Transportation Service Agreements executed pursuant to this Statement shall terminate at the earlier of (i) the date provided for in the applicable Transportation Service Agreement with Shipper, or (ii) the date on which SGCT, in its sole discretion, determines to terminate, on a non-discriminatory basis, all Transportation Service Agreements commenced pursuant to Section 311 (a) (2) of the NGPA. Shipper shall have no contractual remedy, and SGCT shall have no liability, for transportation service related to periods subsequent to the termination of Transportation Service Contracts pursuant to this Article X. XI. Force Majeure If SGCT is rendered unable, wholly or in part, by reason of force majeure or any other cause of any kind not reasonably within its control, to perform or comply with its obligations under this Statement or Transportation Service Agreements executed pursuant to this Statement, then SGCT’s obligations shall be suspended during the continuance of such inability and SGCT shall not be liable in damages during the continuance of any inability so caused, provided such cause shall so far as possible be remedied with all reasonable dispatch. Settlement of strikes, lockouts, and labor disputes affecting SGCT shall be wholly within SGCT’s discretion and the above requirement that any force majeure be remedied with all reasonable dispatch shall not require the settlement of strikes, lockouts, or labor disputes by acceding to the demands of an opposing person when such cause is inadvisable. The term “force majeure” shall mean, cover, and include, but shall not be limited to, the following: acts of God or acts of providence, including without limitation epidemics, landslides, hurricanes, floods, washouts, lightning, earthquakes, storm warnings, perils of the sea, extreme heat or extreme cold, or any other adverse weather conditions; fire, accidents, mechanical breakdowns of, malfunctions of or necessities for making repairs or alterations to furnaces, reactors, plant installations, machinery, lines of pipe, pumps, compressors, valves, gauges or any of the equipment therein or thereon; acts of civil disorder including without limitation, acts of a public enemy, acts of war (declared or undeclared), blockades, insurrections, riots, mass protests or demonstrations and threats of any 10 of the foregoing, and police action in connection with or the reaction to any such acts of civil disorder which directly or indirectly contributes to or results in SGCT’s inability to perform its obligations, inability to obtain or delay in obtaining rights of way, permits, necessary materials or supplies to construct, maintain or operate any facilities required for the performance of any obligations, when any such inability directly or indirectly contributes to or results in SGCT’s inability to perform its obligations; any act or omission by third parties; and any laws, orders, rules, regulations, acts of restraints of any governmental body or authority, civil or military; any other causes, whether of the kind herein enumerated or otherwise, not reasonably within the control of SGCT, and which by the exercise of due diligence CGNGC is unable wholly or in part, to prevent or overcome. XII. Governmental Actions Notwithstanding any other provisions of this Statement, if any governmental authority takes any action as to SGCT that results in the imposition upon the transportation services described herein of terms or conditions that are, in SGCT’s sole opinion, unduly burdensome and unacceptable and/or that subject or are otherwise designed to subject SGCT to greater or different regulation or jurisdiction than that existing on the date the transportation service commenced, then upon written notice given to Shipper, SGCT may terminate the transportation service effective one (1) day prior to the effective date of such governmental action. XIII. Assignment of Transportation Service Agreements No Shipper may assign any rights under any Transportation Service Agreement subject to this Statement of Operating Conditions, without the prior written consent of SGCT. In the event of Shipper’s noncompliance with this paragraph, SGCT may terminate the Transportation Service Agreement. XIV. Waiver; Modification SGCT may waive, modify, or supplement the conditions set forth in this Statement, without undue discrimination or preference, and without consent from any Shippers, when in SGCT’s reasonable, judgment such action is necessary or appropriate or consistent with reasonable business practices, and SGCT shall be without liability to any Shipper for such action. XV. Effective Date Unless otherwise provided by the Commission and except as otherwise provided herein, this Statement of Operation shall become effective the date filed with the Commission. 11 Rate Summary Southcross Gulf Coast Transmission Ltd. currently has a rate of $0.25 per MMBtu and this rate for interruptible transportation service has been deemed just and reasonable, fair and equitable and not in excess of a cost-based rate by the Texas Railroad Commission by order dated April 18, 1994.a
